2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 72
BY SENATOR BOUDREAUX
CONDOLENCES. Expresses sincere and heartfelt condolences on the passing of William
F. "Charlie" McCarthy.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the sincere and heartfelt condolences of the Senate of the Legislature of
3 Louisiana on the occasion of the passing of William F. "Charlie" McCarthy and to
4 celebrate his long life of service, leadership, dedication, and achievement.
5 WHEREAS, it is with deep sadness and profound sorrow that the members of the
6 Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana have learned of the passing of William F. "Charlie"
7 McCarthy on Friday, July 18, 2025, at his home in Baton Rouge, Louisiana, at the
8 remarkable age of 102; and
9 WHEREAS, Charlie McCarthy was born on August 7, 1922, in Fall River,
10 Massachusetts, and lived a life marked by service, leadership, dedication, and achievement
11 across a variety of fields; and
12 WHEREAS, a true patriot, Charlie honorably served his country in the United States
13 Navy as a member of the Navy Amphibious Forces during World War II from 1942 until
14 1945, and after the war he returned to Southeastern Louisiana College and subsequently
15 began his first career as a State Farm Agent in Independence, Louisiana, a tenure that
16 spanned two decades; and
17 WHEREAS, Charlie lived out his true passion by serving for thirty years as a
18 basketball official in the Southeastern Conference (SEC) where he was widely known and
