1 admired for his enthusiasm and excellence in officiating, a role to which he brought fairness,
2 professionalism, and a deep knowledge of the game; and
3 WHEREAS, even after his time on the court, Charlie continued contributing to the
4 sport as he served for five years as an observer for the National Basketball Association
5 taking notes at NBA games, providing valuable insights to help improve the performance
6 of active referees and was later invited by the SEC to serve in a similar capacity; and
7 WHEREAS, Charlie's dedication extended beyond the basketball court and his
8 insurance career to his family, and he leaves behind a loving legacy that includes his beloved
9 wife of seventy-five years, Frances Marie "Frankie" McCarthy; son and daughter-in-law,
10 William F. McCarthy Jr. and Jackie P. McCarthy; son and daughter-in-law, Robert
11 McCarthy and Terri Breaux McCarthy; daughter and son–in-law, Mary Clare Horgan and
12 Porter Smith Horgan; his grandchildren, Lainey T. Major (Taylor Major), Kandice Clare
13 Trock (Harris Evan Trock), Kristen Clare Drouant (Ross Drouant), and Chloe Clare
14 McCarthy; and his great-grandchildren, Levi Elaina Major, MiMi Clare Trock, Ruby Clare
15 Trock; William McCarthy Drouant, Griffen Robert Drouant, Wells Parker Drouant, and
16 Jones Robert Trock; and
17 WHEREAS, Charlie was preceded in death by his parents, William McCarthy and
18 Clara Jordan McCarthy; and
19 WHEREAS, William F. "Charlie" McCarthy will be missed by all who knew him,
20 but his legacy of integrity, commitment, and love will live on in his family, friends, and all
21 who cherished him.
22 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
23 does hereby extend sincere and heartfelt condolences to the family and friends of William
24 F. "Charlie" McCarthy on the occasion of his passing and does hereby recognize and record
25 for posterity the rich life and contributions of Charlie's extraordinary life of service to his
26 country, community, and family.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
28 Frances Marie "Frankie" McCarthy.
